  "text": "Intuitively, for every given time interval [t j−1 , t j ], the set O j contains an (R, h) pair such that R overapproximates the reachable set for the mode h in the given interval duration. In a previous work on verification using simulations [CITATION_1] , an algorithm that computes overapproximation of the reachable set via sampled executions and annotations is presented. The procedure, called ComputeReachTube, takes as input the initial set Θ, switching signals S, partitioning parameter δ, simulation error , and time step τ . It compute the sequence ψ and error such that ψ is a (Θ, S, , τ )-ReachT ube. The procedure is outline below.",
